## Play Function Patterns

### Pattern 1: Render Check

**Purpose:** Verify web component renders in DOM

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Verify component renders', async () => {
    const element = await canvas.findByRole('button');
    await expect(element).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
}
```

**IMPORTANT:** Always use `findBy*` (async) — web components render asynchronously.

### Pattern 2: Click Interaction

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Click button', async () => {
    const button = await canvas.findByRole('button');
    await userEvent.click(button);
  });
}
```

### Pattern 3: Custom Event Testing (Stencil @Event)

Stencil components emit custom events (e.g., `buttonClick`, `inputChange`). Testing these requires direct event listeners:

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Verify custom event emits on click', async () => {
    const button = await canvas.findByRole('button');
    let eventFired = false;

    button.addEventListener('buttonClick', () => {
      eventFired = true;
    }, { once: true });

    await userEvent.click(button);
    await expect(eventFired).toBe(true);
  });
}
```

### Pattern 4: Form Input

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Type in text input', async () => {
    const input = await canvas.findByRole('textbox');
    await userEvent.type(input, 'Test value');
    await expect(input).toHaveValue('Test value');
  });
}
```

### Pattern 5: Keyboard Navigation

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Navigate with Tab', async () => {
    const firstElement = await canvas.findByRole('button');
    firstElement.focus();
    await expect(firstElement).toHaveFocus();

    await userEvent.keyboard('{Tab}');
  });

  await step('Activate with Enter', async () => {
    await userEvent.keyboard('{Enter}');
  });
}
```

### Pattern 6: State Changes (Toggle/Switch)

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Toggle switch', async () => {
    const toggle = await canvas.findByRole('switch');
    await expect(toggle).not.toBeChecked();

    await userEvent.click(toggle);
    await expect(toggle).toBeChecked();
  });
}
```

### Pattern 7: Dropdown/Select

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Open dropdown', async () => {
    const select = await canvas.findByRole('combobox');
    await userEvent.click(select);
  });

  await step('Select option', async () => {
    const option = await canvas.findByRole('option', { name: 'Option 2' });
    await userEvent.click(option);
  });
}
```

### Pattern 8: Multi-Step Interaction

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Step 1: Open accordion', async () => {
    const header = await canvas.findByRole('button', { name: /section 1/i });
    await userEvent.click(header);
  });

  await step('Step 2: Verify content visible', async () => {
    const content = await canvas.findByText('Accordion content');
    await expect(content).toBeVisible();
  });

  await step('Step 3: Close accordion', async () => {
    const header = await canvas.findByRole('button', { name: /section 1/i });
    await userEvent.click(header);
  });
}
```

