## Accessibility Testing Patterns

### Pattern 9: ARIA Attributes

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Verify ARIA attributes', async () => {
    const button = await canvas.findByRole('button');
    await expect(button).toHaveAttribute('aria-label', 'Close dialog');
  });

  await step('Verify ARIA state changes', async () => {
    const button = await canvas.findByRole('button');
    await userEvent.click(button);
    await expect(button).toHaveAttribute('aria-pressed', 'true');
  });
}
```

### Pattern 10: Focus Management

```typescript
play: async ({ canvasElement, step }) => {
  const canvas = within(canvasElement);

  await step('Verify focus management', async () => {
    const input = await canvas.findByRole('textbox');
    input.focus();
    await expect(input).toHaveFocus();
  });

  await step('Tab to next element', async () => {
    await userEvent.keyboard('{Tab}');
    const nextElement = document.activeElement;
    await expect(nextElement).toBeTruthy();
  });
}
```

