## Common Pitfalls

### Pitfall 1: Using Sync Queries

```typescript
// Bad — sync query may fail for web components
const button = canvas.getByRole('button');

// Good — async query waits for render
const button = await canvas.findByRole('button');
```

### Pitfall 2: Hard-Coded Timing

```typescript
// Bad — brittle timing
await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));

// Good — wait for specific condition
await canvas.findByText('Loaded');
```

### Pitfall 3: Testing Implementation Details

```typescript
// Bad — testing CSS class names
expect(button).toHaveClass('btn-primary');

// Good — testing behavior and ARIA
expect(button).toHaveAttribute('aria-pressed', 'true');
```

### Pitfall 4: Not Handling Shadow DOM

Some Stencil components render content inside Shadow DOM. The `within(canvasElement)` scope
may not reach into Shadow DOM. For these cases, consult **File 3 (Web Components Specifics)**.

